{
  "name": "Grappling Hook",
  "type": "tool",
  "img": "icons/tools/fishing/hook-multi-steel-brown.webp",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><span dir=\"ltr\">You can throw a grappling hook with a rope tied to it to make a climb easier, when wall walking is out of the question.</span></p><p><span dir=\"ltr\">To anchor a grappling hook, make a Strength or Dexterity (Survival) check vs the anchors DC, which is based on the target anchoring condition.</span></p><p><span dir=\"ltr\">On a success, your hook has a firm hold, but if you fail by 5 or more, the hook seems like it will hold but actually falls when you're partway up.</span></p><img src=\"systems/n5eb/assets/Icons%20%26%20Images/Cheat%20Sheet/Grappling%20Hook%20DC.png\" /><p></p><p></p>",
